# PDF to PPT Generator

AI pipeline that converts teaching PDFs into PowerPoint slides.

## Layout

- `backend/` — FastAPI server, agents, pipeline (`backend/pipeline/`), PPTX generation
- `frontend/` — Next.js UI
- `run_pipeline.py` — CLI runner (no server); adds `backend/` to `sys.path`
- `assets/` — reference PPTs, sample PDFs
- `docs/input/` and `docs/output/` — test PDFs and sample outputs

## Run locally

```bash
# Backend API
cd backend && source .venv/bin/activate && uvicorn app:app --reload

# Pipeline CLI (from repo root)
.venv/bin/python run_pipeline.py

# Frontend
cd frontend && npm run dev
```

## Conventions

- Python venv lives at repo root (`.venv/`) or in `backend/.venv/`
- Secrets in `.env` — never commit
- Pipeline entry: `backend/pipeline/orchestrator.py` → `run_pipeline_async()`
- Keep changes minimal; match existing agent/pipeline patterns in `backend/agents/`
